<p><b>Is there an official ASL dictionary?</b> The Gallaudet Children's Dictionary of American Sign Language is the standard ASL reference for children, their parents, and their teachers. For more information about American Sign Language and related books, visit Gallaudet University Press.</p>
<p><b>What is the ASL dictionary for give?</b> Description. To sign "give" in American Sign Language(ASL): hold your thumb to all your fingers together on your dominant hand, and move your hand away from your body. The motion looks like you are giving the listener something.</p>
