<p><b>What is the word in in ASL?</b> To do the basic sign for "in," close the fingers of your dominant hand hand, form your non-dominant hand into a "C," and place the fingers of your dominant hand into the "C" hand.</p>
<p><b>Are ASL translators deaf?</b> The first major difference is that ASL interpreters are typically hearing individuals whereas CDIs are born deaf or hard of hearing. ASL interpreters must go through extensive training to provide top-notch interpreter services for the deaf community.</p>
